data.description: Super charming 2 bedroom/ 2 bath manufactured home. This mostly flat 4.3 acre parcel is fenced and cross fenced for big and small animals. The large pasture area does need some fencing put back up but there is a small arena to practice in. Black creek is a seasonal creek that runs across a portion of the back property line and so does the community Pedestrian/ Equestrian Trail. This home boasts an open floor plan with high ceilings, large windows and a wood burning fireplace. The kitchen has a nice layout with plenty of cabinets and a breakfast bar. The separate dining area has a slider that leads to a screened in back porch with access to the back yard. The primary bedroom is nice sized with a slider that takes you out onto your own covered deck for morning coffee. There is plenty of parking for all your needs and a couple of super cute outbuildings. With this amount of property there is room for maintaining animals and a garden making this a true haven for the homesteaders and animal enthusiasts. Located within the Copper Cove Subdivision you'll enjoy all the amenities of Black Creek Community park and have access to Lake Tulloch. You can launch your watercraft or just hang out to barbeque and swim in the day use area. Only hours away from the bay area with lots of outdoor activities, restaurant's and wine tasting both here and up the hill. Call today to schedule your appointment to see!!
